	abstract = {The goal of this article is to provide a method that makes use of a face recognition-powered unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV). The goal of this approach is to make it easier for law enforcement to identify suspects, track down missing persons, verify identities, and carry out age-based monitoring. A facial recognition system is an electronic tool that uses AI to recognise people by their faces. Identity verification often makes use of facial recognition technologies. The facial features of a picture are analysed in this procedure. This research details the steps required to design, build, and test an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) integrated with a camera and face recognition software. The UAV is used as a remote control for a robot equipped with Bluetooth technology. The suggested method proves it can adapt to different drone orientations. Drone camera angles in all 37 directions have an accuracy of 99.3 percent, proving this point. Recovery activities, rescue missions, occurrence inquiries, offender assessment, and crowd surveillance are just a few examples of how specialised software may aid law enforcement in their investigative work. © 2023 IEEE.},
